# Implementation Plan: Question Validation, Analytics, & Security

This document outlines the approach to address the 6 primary requirements specified in `Validating questions.txt`.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Data Harvesting & Analytics:** Tracking real-time "Time spent per topic" requires injecting a telemetry tracker into the Workspace that "pings" your Firestore database periodically or on unmount. We will need to design this schema carefully to avoid huge Firebase bandwidth costs.
> **Archetype Metadata:** Currently, your React app doesn't know *what* archetypes exist; it only asks your Python backend to generate them. To show "a dashboard with the number of archetypes", we will need to add a new endpoint to your Python backend (e.g., `/api/accounting/metadata`) that returns the available archetypes. For *this plan*, we will build the UI assuming you know the archetype seed, and outline the backend work needed.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Phase A: Question Validation Sandbox (SuperAdmin)

We will build a dedicated "Validation Workspace" inside your Admin dashboard. This will allow you to select a Grade (10/11/12), Subskill, and input a specific Seed ID. It will then fetch the question from your Python backend and render it *exactly* using the student's `Grade12AccountingScaffold` (or equivalent) component.

#### [MODIFY] `src/components/forms/AdminForms.jsx`
- Add a new `QuestionValidator` component interface.
- Includes dropdowns for Grade, Subskill, and an input for `Seed`.
- Introduce a "Test Question" button that fetches the question payload and mounts the actual student workspace component (e.g., `Grade12AccountingScaffold`) inside the Admin panel for true 1:1 evaluation.

#### [MODIFY] `src/components/admin/AdminView.jsx`
- Add routing for the new `QuestionValidator` view.

---

### Phase B: Analytics Dashboard Updates

We will expand the existing `SystemAnalytics` component to pull real-time subscription counts and layout the foundation for "Time Spent" metrics.

#### [MODIFY] `src/components/forms/AdminForms.jsx` (SystemAnalytics)
- Query the `users` collection to count active subscriptions vs standard/free users.
- Add UI placeholder charts for "Average Time per Topic" (which will populate once the telemetry data pipeline is in place).

---

### Phase C: Role Locking & Institutional Separation

Currently, the `Header.jsx` toggle (Student/Teacher/Admin) is *already* exclusively visible to users with `isSuperAdmin: true`. Normal subscribers cannot see this toggle. We will solidify this by implementing stricter Firestore rules and outlining Institutional Admin roles.

#### [NEW] `firestore.rules` (Security Implementation)
- We need to establish strict server-side rules. Currently, if a tech-savvy student opens Chrome DevTools, they could potentially modify their own `user` document to change their role to `admin` or extend their `subscriptionExpiry`.
- We will draft secure rules that enforce: only SuperAdmins can write to `subscriptionExpiry` or `role`.

#### Architecture Updates
- **Role Segregation:** We will formalize 4 roles: `student`, `teacher`, `schooladmin`, and `superadmin`. Your emails are `superadmin`. For future B2B sales, `schooladmin` will get a restricted version of the Admin dashboard (managing only their specific students), completely separated from the Question Validator and global Analytics.

